snippet.title: Johnny Depp Loses Court Case Against Newspaper That Called Him a â€˜Wife Beaterâ€™
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp leaves Fantastic Beasts film franchise
Johnny Depp Breaks His Silence On Losing Amber Heard Domestic Violence Case

Johnny Depp Forced to Exit â€˜Fantastic Beastsâ€™ Franchise




LONDON â€” Johnny Depp on Monday lost his court case against a British newspaper that called him a â€œwife beaterâ€ and claimed there was â€œoverwhelming evidenceâ€ that he had assaulted the actress Amber Heard repeatedly during their marriage.
Mr. Deppâ€™s assaults included head-butting Ms. Heard, repeatedly hitting her and tearing out clumps of her hair, wrote Andrew Nicol, the British judge who heard the case, in a ruling issued online on Monday. In dismissing the case, he said the defendants had shown that what they published was â€œsubstantially true.â€
The assaults â€œmust have been terrifying,â€ the judge wrote regarding incidents in March 2015 in Australia, in which Ms. Heard said that Mr. Depp assaulted her several times, including smashing a telephone beside her face. â€œI accept that Mr. Depp put her in fear of her life,â€ the judge wrote.
The judge also acknowledged the risk Ms. Heard
 had taken in speaking up about the violence. â€œI also accept that Ms. Heardâ€™s allegations have had a negative effect on her career as an actor and activist,â€ he said.
